        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 7:32PM CDT until June 27 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>SVRBMX

The National Weather Service in Birmingham has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Jefferson County in central Alabama...

* Until 815 PM CDT.

* At 732 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Irondale,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Birmingham, Vestavia Hills, Mountain Brook, Trussville, Irondale,
Leeds, Center Point, Tarrant, Shops of Grand River, Kingston,
Alton, Barber Motorsports Park, Birmingham Airport, Cahaba Heights,
Lake Purdy, Brook Highland, Grants Mill Road Bridge, Birmingham
Race Course, Ruffner Mountain, and Liberty Park.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
